📋 Submission Requirements
Submit all of the following via this bounty page by April 6, all the submissions must be made through Earn to be eligible:

🎥 Demo/Pitch Video (max 3 min) 
Walk us through your strategy, your edge, and how it operates on Ranger Earn.

📄 Strategy Documentation 
Explain your strategy thesis, how it works in practice, and your risk management approach — including drawdown limits, position sizing, and rebalancing logic.

💻 Code Repository 
Open-source repos are encouraged, but you may keep your repo private. If your repo is private, you are required to add @jakeyvee on GitHub so that organizers and judges can review your code. Submissions without verifiable code will not be considered.

🔗 On-chain Verification 
Submit the wallet address or vault address used during the hackathon build window (Mar 9 – Apr 6). We will verify trade activity and performance directly on-chain via Solscan.

📊 CEX Strategy Verification (if applicable) 
If your strategy involves CEX execution, submit:

Trade history CSV export from your exchange (Binance, OKX, Bybit, etc.)

A read-only API key for further verification

Why we require this: Seed TVL prizes are awarded based on verified strategy performance. On-chain addresses and CEX trade history allow us to confirm that trades occurred within the hackathon window, that PnL is real, and that your strategy matches your documentation. This protects the integrity of the competition and ensures fair judging for all participants.

Live performance during the hackathon period (Mar 9–Apr 6) is preferred, but backtested results are accepted.

⚖️ Judging Criteria
Strategy Quality & Edge – Genuine alpha or defensible thesis. Differentiated approach.

Risk Management – Drawdown limits, liquidation protection, position sizing, rebalancing.

Technical Implementation – Code quality, adaptor integration, vault architecture, security.

Production Viability – Realistic deployment path, scalability, operational complexity.

Novelty & Innovation – New primitives, creative protocol combinations, ecosystem contribution.

